observationText: Neurofibromin was completely absent in Nf1Arg681*/Arg681* MEFs, resulting in hyperactivation of phosphorylated ERK (pERK) levels compared to wild-type controls.
Nf1Arg681*/Arg681* mouse embryos failed to develop past embryonic day 9.5 due to cardiovascular defects, similar to Nf1 null embryos.
